Lunaria's AD Blocker

A simple Chrome extension that blocks unwanted ads and improves browsing speed.

Project Structure

ADblocker/
│
├── manifest.json
├── background.js
├── popup.html
└── icons/
├── icon16.png
├── icon48.png
└── icon128.png

How to  Install (Load Packed Extension)

Download the .crx file

Go to chrome://extensions/

Turn ON "Developer mode" in the top-right corner.

Drag and drop the .crx file into the extensions page.

The extension should now appear in your toolbar.

How to Install (Load Unpacked Extension)

Open Google Chrome (or another Chromium-based browser).

Go to chrome://extensions/

Turn ON "Developer mode" in the top-right corner.

Click "Load unpacked".

Select the ADblocker folder (the one containing manifest.json).

The extension should now appear in your toolbar.

File Descriptions

manifest.json - Defines the extension’s name, version, permissions, and icons.
background.js - Contains background logic such as ad blocking rules.
popup.html - The small window shown when clicking the extension icon.
icons/ - Folder containing the extension’s icons in multiple sizes.

Permissions Used

storage - Saves user preferences.
tabs - Allows the extension to access browser tabs.
webRequest - Lets the extension monitor network requests.
webRequestBlocking - Enables blocking unwanted requests.
host_permissions - Grants access to all websites (<all_urls>).


